According to a statement, Lehasa will be taking on the role of Zakes, an educated young man who chose to follow in his father s footsteps by becoming a drug kingpin.And after serving time in jail, Zakes is out to get his revenge on those who betrayed him. Lehasa is also part of the Gold Diggers season two writing team. So far, he has written nine episodes for the show. Lehasa is no stranger to the small screen. He has previously starred on Rhythm City as Mongezi and has also hosted e.tv s Mgongo music show. Find the hottest celebrity and entertainment news on TshisaLIVE or follow TshisaLIVE on Facebook and Twitter.